-- WI-744 control: the exact twin of bad-import-query.anthill — same shape, only
-- the import differs. Pins that the sibling's block is attributable to the
-- unresolved import and to nothing else about this file's structure.
--
-- The fact is TOP-LEVEL on purpose: `collect_queries` scans `parsed.items` for
-- `Item::Fact`, so a fact nested in a namespace is invisible to it ("no fact
-- declarations found"). The namespace is here only to host an import — which is
-- the only way to write one, since the `-i` flag prepends a bare top-level
-- `import` line that is not valid grammar.
namespace probe.q
  import anthill.prelude.String
end

fact probe.db.Person.mk(name: ?n, age: ?a)
